description:
## Bug

In tui/src/event.rs handle_slash() for the /cat command (line ~1291):

    let truncated = if bytes.len() > 4096 {
        &bytes[..4096]
    } else {
        &bytes
    };
    let content = String::from_utf8_lossy(truncated).to_string();

The raw byte slice is cut at byte 4096 without checking whether 4096 is a valid UTF-8 character boundary. from_utf8_lossy() replaces the invalid trailing bytes with U+FFFD (replacement character), silently corrupting the message content.

Contrast with the /! command in the same file (line ~1243-1252) which correctly finds the last valid char boundary at or before byte 4096 using char_indices().

## Impact

If the file contains a multi-byte UTF-8 character that spans the 4096-byte boundary, the message sent to the relay contains a replacement character instead of the actual character, causing silent data corruption.

## Fix

Apply the same char-boundary-finding logic as the /! command to /cat's truncation path.
